    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.8"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Morningside College Seal</figDesc>
                        <p><unclear/></p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">DEPARTMENT OF 
                        <lb/>
                    HISTORY AND POLITICAL SCIENCE</hi> 
                        <lb/>
                    
                    Morningside College 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">SIOUX CITY, IOWA</hi> 51106
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Jan. 14, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The Convocation Committee is interestd in having you speak to our student body in the 1972<del>2</del><add>-</add>73 school year. There is a good deal of interest in Indian studies on our campus, and your appearance would be welcomed by our students.</p> 
                
                <p>If you deal exclusively through an agent, would you put me in touch with that agent so we can negotiate though him.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>David Van Engelenhoven</signed>
                    <signed>David Van Engelenhoven
                    Chairman, Convocations Comm.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
